title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson 744-VR 44 Mag
postcontent: Dan Wesson revolver in the powerful 44 Magnum. This is the model 744 fitted with a 10 inch vent ribbed barrel. This is an early gun made by Dan Wesson in Monson MA., before they were acquired by CZ. These guns were famous for their interchangeability. The barrels easily screw off and you can switch lengths depending on what you need. The guns are also know for their cylinder lockup. The cylinder release is locked on the crane instead of on the side of the receiver. This gun is in great condition. The grips are a nice hardwood. There are some light impressions, but no chips or cracks. The gun has some light handling marks, but nothing major. There is a light cylinder ring. The action is smooth. The double action pull is short and clean, and the gun locks up tight. This is a great revolver for hunting, or just another great addition to the collection. Don't miss out on this great, powerful handgun. Low Start, No Reserve. Buyer pays shipping,

title: For Sale:  Megastar .45 Semi-auto Pistol
postcontent: Megastar ,45 caliber semi-auto pistol.  General Information:  The Megastar pistol is a heavy, powerful pistol, which appeared on the markets in 1993.  It was designed and manufactured by the Spanish company Star Bonifacio Echeverris SA, and its designis based on the previous guns by the same manufacturer, such as Star 30M.  Production of the Megastar was completed in the late 1990s. Megastar is a recoil operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistol.  It uses a Browning High-Power type locking system with tilting barrel.  Megastar is a hammer fired pistol, with double action trigger and ambidextrous, slide mounted safety-decocker lever.  The safety lever has three positions:  upper one for "fire" mode, red dot is shown, medium one for "safe" mode, this withdraws and locks the firing pin and the lower one for safe decocking (after decocking safety springs back to the "safe" position).  Megastar also features a magazine disconnect safety which does not allow to fire the gun without the magazine in place.  Megastar slide and frame are made from steel, and like other latest Star pistols, Megastar has internal slide rails, instead of more usual external rails.  This pistol features non-adjustable sights.  Magazine capacity is quite impressive, especially when speaking about the period of the early 1990s, and is 12 rounds of .45 ACP.Overall, Megastar represents one of the strongest designsin auto-pistols, heavy but powerful and built to last forever.  Heavy weight also helpsto control the recoilof the powerful cartridge used.
